text: Exeter is a town in Rockingham County, New Hampshire, United States. As of the 2020 census, 16,049 people lived there. It is home to Phillips Exeter Academy, a famous private boarding school. ==Other websites== * * Exeter Historical Society * SAU 16, Exeter Area School District * Exeter Public Library Category:Towns in New Hampshire Category:1638 establishments in North America
